In packages/serverless-offline-sqs/src/sqs.js, normalize string input before spreading and drop arn so the override wins:

const resolveQueueName = (options, rawSqsEventDefinition) => {
  if (!(options && options.queueName)) return rawSqsEventDefinition;
  const base =
    typeof rawSqsEventDefinition === 'string'
      ? {arn: rawSqsEventDefinition}
      : rawSqsEventDefinition;
  return {...omit(['arn'], base), queueName: options.queueName};
};

(omit is already imported from lodash/fp in sqs.js.) This yields a clean def object (no char-indexed keys) and makes the override actually win for both the string-ARN and object-with-arn forms, since stripping arn forces SQSEventDefinition's switch to use the .queueName branch. Add a test asserting the resolved def has no numeric keys (e.g. t.deepEqual(Object.keys(resolved).sort(), ['queueName'])) and that a constructed SQSEventDefinition has no stray numeric keys, to lock the regression.

